Black; antenna brown or brown-testaceous, except scape and pedicel yellow (
Fig. 9A
). Antennomeres in following proportions: 4:3:4:4:5:5:4.5:4:4:6. Head dull, granulate (
Fig. 9A, B
); frontal line incomplete, only a trace present in anterior third of frons (
Fig. 9A
). Mesoscutum dull, granulate (
Fig. 9C
); notauli reaching approximately 0.4 × length of mesoscutum (
Fig. 9C
); metapectal-propodeal complex with disc reticulate rugose (
Fig. 9D
); propodeal declivity with wide median area shiny, almost completely unsculptured, surrounded by rugose areolae (
Fig. 9D
). 2r-rs&Rs vein regularly curved (
Fig. 9E
).

Head dull, granulate (
Fig. 10A, B
); frontal line incomplete, only present in anterior third of frons (
Fig. 10A
). Mesoscutum dull, granulate (
Fig. 10C
); notauli reaching approximately 0.4 × length of mesoscutum (
Fig. 10C
); mesoscutellum shiny, slightly granulate (
Fig. 10C
); metanotum shiny, unsculptured; metapectal-propodeal complex dull, with disc reticulate rugose (
Fig. 10D
). Propodeal declivity almost completely shiny, unsculptured, surrounded by numerous rugose areolae. 2r-rs&Rs vein regularly curved (
Fig. 10E
). Distal apex of aedeagus not tridentate; basivolsella with two subdistal bristles and with an outer basal process (
Fig. 3D
).
